programme.title: WA World Indoor Tour Athletics, Torun
programme.desc: Many of the world’s best track and field athletes continue to fine-tune their Olympics preparations as the World Indoor Tour gathers momentum in Poland. Already we have seen great performances this year by sprinter Dina Asher Smith, pole vaulter Holly Bradshaw and middle-distance runners Jemma Reekie, Laura Muir and Elliot Giles, and more of Britain’s best are expected to take to the boards again at this prestigious Copernicus Cup meeting in Torun.

programme.title: Spašavanje vrta 5, ep. 10.
programme.desc: Retired couple David and Joyce’s back garden outside Gloucester looks more like an allotment than a garden. David is a dedicated veg grower, so much of the area is given over to that. But it has become a problem for them both. For Joyce, there’s nowhere shady or pretty to sit and relax, while David, who has back and knee problems, struggles to keep working it. So Charlie and the Rich brothers must make the garden both prettier and more user friendly, all for £3,000.

programme.desc: John Humphrys asks the questions as four more famous faces brave the black chair in another episode of the classic quiz where celebrities donate to their chosen charities. programme.title: Catchpoint 3, ep. 4.

programme.title: Match of the Day
programme.desc: Gary Lineker introduces all the goals, highlights and talking points on another day of Premier League intrigue, including the 289th Merseyside derby between Liverpool and Everton. Champions Liverpool drew 2-2 at Goodison Park earlier this season, with Everton twice coming from behind to rescue a point. Liverpool are on a 23-game unbeaten run against their Merseyside neighbours in all competitions dating back to October 2010.

programme.title: Snaga je u meni
programme.desc: Temeljeno na knjizi Stronger autora Jeffa Baumana, žrtve bombaškog napada za vrijeme Bostonskog maratona 2013. godine. Gyllenhaal glumi preživjelog Jeffa Baumana, koji je u eksploziji izgubio obje noge, ali ne i volju za životom. Bauman se probudio 16. travnja 2013. godine bez nogu. Samo trideset sati prije, bio je okružen masom ljudi na cilju Bostonskog maratona. Prva bomba mu je otišla pod noge dok je čekao da njegova djevojka utrči u cilj. Kada se probudio nekoliko sati nakon operacije,...

Hymns and songs for the season include "In Christ Alone’, `Standing in the Need of Prayer’ and `When I Survey the Wondrous Cross", sung by Faye Simpson, Katie Ritson and the Adventist Vocal Ensemble.

programme.title: Wanted Down Under 14, ep. 10.
programme.desc: Julia Rosin’s dream is to move her family to Australia in the hope of a better lifestyle for their children. Husband Hussein’s not so sure, he has been through a move before and found moving from one country to another difficult. Julia hopes that seeing the houses, work opportunities and lifestyle Brisbane has to offer will change his mind.

programme.title: Bargain Hunt 48, ep. 21.
programme.desc: Charlie Ross presents from Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire. Jonathan Pratt and Colin Young help the teams find three items to take to the auction in Norfolk, and Charlie also pays a visit to the Norfolk Tank Museum.

programme.title: Songs of Praise, Faith and Hospitality
programme.desc: Katherine Jenkins visits L’Abri fellowship in Hampshire to explore Christian faith and hospitality. She finds out about L’Abri’s history and meets a family from Australia who have settled there. Radzi Chinyanganya meets a former stockbroker who found faith and changed career to help house the homeless. Music comes from congregations across the UK, including O Worship the Lord in the Beauty of Holiness and Table of the Lord.

programme.title: Spašavanje vrta 5, ep. 11.
programme.desc: Jacqui, 26 and Yung, 27, moved into their Trowbridge home a year ago. While they have managed to decorate the house, with their busy jobs they have never had time to fix up the tired garden. It’s dull and featureless, with lots of random brickwork. As they admit that they have no idea about gardening, they’ve called in Charlie and the Rich brothers and given them a budget of £3,500 to create a contemporary space with bright coloured flowers, a relaxation area and lots of room for their dog.

programme.title: Pepeljuga
programme.desc: Iako je maćeha (Cate Blanchett) i polusestre maltretiraju, srčana Ella (Lily James) odluči preuzeti odgovornost za svoju sudbinu. Dodajte tomu kraljevski bal, dobru vilu te staklenu cipelicu i odjednom – magija postaje stvarnost! Priča o Pepeljugi prati sudbinu mlade Elle čiji se otac trgovac ponovno oženi nakon smrti njezine majke. Željna pružiti potporu svom voljenom ocu, Ella dočekuje svoju novu maćehu i njezine kćeri Anastasiju i Drisellu u obiteljskoj kući. Ali kad Ellin otac...

programme.title: Sedam svjetova jedan planet, Azija, ep. 2.
programme.desc: Azija je najveći kontinent na našem planetu, kontinent najvećih krajnosti. Proteže se od arktičkoga kruga na sjeveru do tropskih šuma na ekvatoru. Životinje su ovdje suočene s najtoplijim pustinjama, najvišim džunglama i najvrletnijim planinama od svih na planetu. Ali ovaj kontinent nije uvijek izgledao tako. Ovi ekstremni svjetovi nastali su kad se Indija prije 30 milijuna godina sudarila s ostatkom Azije i oblikovala kontinent kakav danas poznajemo. Ovdašnje su se životinje prilagodile...

programme.title: Countryfile, Nene Valley
programme.desc: Tom Heap explores Northamptonshire’s Nene Valley, discovering how a farmer fighting flooding has embraced wetland wildlife to make his land pay. Tom also meets a sheepdog turned search-and-rescue hero and gets hands-on with a project that has unearthed evidence of riverside residents dating back to Neolithic times. Adam is hoping for good news from his ewes as, thanks to scanning, he discovers how many are in lamb.

programme.title: Antiques Roadshow, Windermere Jetty 1
programme.desc: Fiona Bruce and the team are at Windermere Jetty Museum in the Lake District, where finds include a valuable collection of silver trophies awarded to a pioneering woman sailor, a James Bond poster scraped off a wall, a guitar rescued from a skip, a wooden dinghy from the film Swallows and Amazons, and a pair of ’lost’ necklaces with surprising values. Fiona finds out about the daredevils who have attempted to set speed records on the lakes.

programme.title: Bloodlands 1, ep. 1.
programme.desc: The death of Texas student Kerry Kujawa, who left his campus to visit online girlfriend Kelley McCauley in San Antonio. His dumped body was found two weeks later, in April 2000, on a prairie 130 miles away and it later transpired Kelley was a fictional character invented by Kerry’s 32-year-old assailant.

programme.title: Olly Alexander: Growing Up Gay
programme.desc: Figures show that more than 40 percent of LGBT Plus people will experience a significant mental health problem, compared to around 25 percent of the whole population. Olly Alexander explores why the gay community is more vulnerable to mental health issues.
